Trader Vic produced multiple Scorpion versions over the years; the 1947 version was a 12-serving punch with gin and mint. This is the single-serving spec from his 1972 guide.

In an #electric blender{} combine @light Puerto Rican rum{2%oz}, @brandy{1%oz}, @fresh orange juice{2%oz}, @fresh lemon juice{1.5%oz}, @orgeat{0.5%oz}, and @crushed ice{1%cup}.
Blend on low for ~{10%seconds}, then high until slushy, about ~{10%seconds} more.
Pour into a #double old-fashioned glass{} or scorpion bowl.
Garnish with a @gardenia{1} or @orchid{1} and a @mint sprig{1}.
